SIMPLE: heartless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heartless
<hw>Heart"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Without a
heart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You have left me <qex>heartless</qex>; mine is in your bosom.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Destitute of courage; spiritless;
despondent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Heartless</qex> they fought, and quitted soon their
ground.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Heartless</qex> and melancholy.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Irwing.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Destitute of feeling or affection; unsympathetic;
cruel.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>heartless</xex> parasites.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Byron.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Heart"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Heart"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heartlet</ent>⟦br⟧
